race.comment: Tough finish. JUSTDOIT (6) did enough first up at Yarra Valley when running on well from back in the field on a track that suits those on speed. She doesn't win out of turn but has the form last time in to be highly competitive in this. BARDIA'S DREAM (4) resumes. Her form last time in was rock solid, winning her maiden comfortably fresh at Pakenham Synthetic and measuring up in some handy races thereafter. She's open to further improvement this time in and looks a key chance. LONGTIMEDREAMING (1) was much better second up here off a mediocre return and has claims off that. KILCARN (13) won her maiden at the second time of asking, scoring narrowly at Colac. This is harder but she could measure up. BONFIRE JIMMY (7) similarly won his maiden last time and has claims.
